{"type":"message","id":"32b6c3f9","parentId":"eec63027","timestamp":"2026-03-27T01:31:43.954Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_8cfadb96778146f78fa94dfd","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\r\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-03-26T07:05:31.406Z\",\r\n  \"lookbackHours\": 24,\r\n  \"x\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"source\": \"x\",\r\n      \"name\": \"Andrej Karpathy\",\r\n      \"handle\": \"karpathy\",\r\n      \"bio\": \"I like to train large deep neural nets. Previously Director of AI @ Tesla, founding team @ OpenAI, PhD @ Stanford.\",\r\n      \"tweets\": [\r\n        {\r\n          \"id\": \"2036841069636370467\",\r\n          \"text\": \"(I cycle through all LLMs over time and all of them seem to do this so it's not any particular implementation but something deeper, e.g. maybe during training, a lot of the information in the context window is relevant to the task, so the LLMs develop a bias to use what is given, then at test time overfit to anything that happens to RAG its way there via a memory feature (?))\",\r\n          \"createdAt\": \"2026-03-25T16:22:08.000Z\",\r\n          \"url\": \"https://x.com/karpathy/status/2036841069636370467\",\r\n          \"likes\": 1241,\r\n          \"retweets\": 30,\r\n          \"replies\": 103,\r\n          \"isQuote\": false,\r\n          \"quotedTweetId\": null"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2166,"aggregated":"{\r\n  \"generatedAt\": \"2026-03-26T07:05:31.406Z\",\r\n  \"lookbackHours\": 24,\r\n  \"x\": [\r\n    {\r\n      \"source\": \"x\",\r\n      \"name\": \"Andrej Karpathy\",\r\n      \"handle\": \"karpathy\",\r\n      \"bio\": \"I like to train large deep neural nets. Previously Director of AI @ Tesla, founding team @ OpenAI, PhD @ Stanford.\",\r\n      \"tweets\": [\r\n        {\r\n          \"id\": \"2036841069636370467\",\r\n          \"text\": \"(I cycle through all LLMs over time and all of them seem to do this so it's not any particular implementation bu